#compdef gitvan
# ============================================================================
# _gitvan — zsh completion for **gitvan** — seanchatmangpt/gitvan, the
#            **Git-native workflow automation platform** that treats
#            the git repository itself as the orchestration substrate.
#            Workflows are declared in Turtle / RDF `.ttl` files
#            living inside the repo at `.gitvan/workflows/*.ttl` and
#            triggered by git events (commit / push / merge) +
#            cron schedules + manual `gitvan workflow run` calls.
#            Behind the scenes uses semantic graph technology
#            (Comunica SPARQL engine + N3.js Turtle parser + UnRDF)
#            for federated queries and reactive hooks.  Pure-JS Git
#            operations via **isomorphic-git**, the canonical pure-
#            JavaScript Git implementation that runs identically in
#            Node and browsers.  TS-Node=180 **CLOSES** Axis 125 at
#            1/1/1 — triple-180 landmark (Rust=180 + Go=180 +
#            TS-Node=180) + 118th axis closed.
# ============================================================================
#
# UPSTREAM
#   Repository : https://github.com/seanchatmangpt/gitvan
#   Maintainer : Sean Chatman (seanchatmangpt on GitHub);  founder
#                 of multiple AI/automation startups;  GitVan is the
#                 successor evolution of an earlier "git-as-runtime"
#                 prototype, redesigned around semantic-graph
#                 primitives + Citty (UnJS's typed CLI framework) +
#                 Nuxt-team's UnJS ecosystem
#   License    : Apache-2.0
#   Stars      : 200+ on github.com/seanchatmangpt/gitvan
#   Language   : TypeScript / Node ESM  (citty for the CLI surface +
#                 isomorphic-git ^1.27.1 for pure-JS Git operations +
#                 N3 for Turtle/RDF parsing + Comunica for SPARQL +
#                 Bree for in-process job scheduling +
#                 node-cron for cron expressions + memfs for the
#                 in-memory filesystem layer + Nunjucks for
#                 template rendering)
#   Binary     : gitvan  (`npm install -g gitvan` →
#                 `./dist/bin/gitvan.mjs`)
#   Last push  : 2026-06-02
#
# WHAT IT IS
#   GitVan is the **git-native workflow automation system** —
#   structurally adjacent to:
#
#     • **GitHub Actions** — but workflows live in `.gitvan/` as
#       Turtle/RDF instead of `.github/workflows/*.yml` as YAML,
#       and the runtime is the local repo (no SaaS dependency)
#     • **Argo Workflows** — but workflows are RDF graphs queried
#       via SPARQL instead of Kubernetes CRDs
#     • **Temporal / Cadence** — but the persistence layer is
#       git history itself (every workflow execution becomes a
#       git commit;  audit trail is `git log`)
#     • **n8n / Zapier** — but the trigger surface is git events,
#       not webhook URLs
#     • **Nx / Turborepo** — but the task graph is declared as a
#       knowledge graph instead of project.json
#
#   Subcommand surface (22 top-level commands, most with nested
#   subcommands):
#
#   Core workflow + event commands:
#     • daemon                        long-running daemon that
#                                     watches git events
#         start / stop / status /
#         restart
#     • event                         simulate or replay git
#                                     events
#     • cron                          cron-driven workflow
#                                     scheduler
#         list / start / dry-run /
#         status
#     • audit                         build/inspect audit logs
#                                     of workflow executions
#     • hooks                         Knowledge Hooks (the
#                                     reactive-query subsystem)
#         list / evaluate / validate /
#         stats / refresh
#     • workflow                      manage workflow .ttl files
#         list / run / validate /
#         create / stats
#     • jtbd                          Jobs-To-Be-Done (the
#                                     intent-driven workflow
#                                     primitive)
#     • cleanroom                     reproducible build env
#         build / test
#
#   Job + schedule management:
#     • job                           manage Bree-backed jobs
#     • schedule                      cron-schedule management
#         list / apply / enable /
#         disable
#     • worktree                      git worktree management
#         list / create / remove /
#         prune / repair / info
#     • submodule                     git submodule helpers
#         status / check / init /
#         update / sync / verify
#
#   Project management:
#     • init                          initialize gitvan in repo
#     • setup                         setup gitvan globals
#     • save                          quick-save commit
#     • ensure                        idempotent state assertion
#
#   Package + marketplace:
#     • pack                          install a gitvan pack
#     • marketplace                   pack registry interaction
#     • scaffold                      scaffold new components
#     • compose                       gitvan-as-docker-compose
#
#   AI + automation:
#     • chat                          conversational gitvan
#                                     interface
#     • llm                           LLM-driven workflow
#                                     generation
#         generate / job
#
#   RevOps analytics:
#     • revops                        revenue-ops analytics
#         metrics / report / health /
#         forecast / customers
#
#   Studio + IDE integration:
#     • studio                        Next.js-based gitvan IDE
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from `src/cli.mjs` citty
#                       `defineCommand({ subCommands: { ... }})`
#                       declarations + each
#                       `src/cli/commands/<name>.mjs` file's
#                       `defineCommand({ args: { ... }})`
#                       declarations;  extracted via
#                       raw.githubusercontent.com fetch of each
#                       file)
#
#   gitvan [GLOBAL OPTIONS] <COMMAND> [SUBCOMMAND] [ARGS...]
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `seanchatmangpt/gitvan`'s `package.json` declares a **direct**
#   dependency on `isomorphic-git@^1.27.1`.  The git-operation
#   layer at `src/git-native/` + `src/git-lifecycle/` uses typed
#   `git.clone({fs, http, dir, url, ref, singleBranch, depth})` to
#   shallow-clone pack repos, typed `git.log({fs, dir, ref, depth})`
#   to walk commit history for workflow-trigger event detection,
#   typed `git.listFiles({fs, dir, ref})` to enumerate the working
#   tree, typed `git.readBlob({fs, dir, oid, filepath})` to fetch
#   workflow `.ttl` files at specific commits (the "workflow at
#   version" semantic), typed `git.statusMatrix({fs, dir})` to
#   detect dirty paths, typed `git.commit({fs, dir, author,
#   message})` to materialize workflow-output commits, and typed
#   `git.push({fs, http, dir, remote, ref, onAuth})` for remote
#   propagation.
#
#   **isomorphic-git** (`isomorphic-git` on npm) is **THE canonical
#   pure-JavaScript Git implementation** — William Hilton's
#   reference pure-TS implementation of the Git protocol stack +
#   on-disk format, written from scratch in idiomatic ES modules
#   with the explicit goal of running identically in Node AND in
#   browsers (the eponymous "isomorphic" property).  In active
#   development since 2017 with 7,000+ ★ on github.com/
#   isomorphic-git/isomorphic-git.  Clocks 800,000+ weekly
#   downloads on npm — the dominant pure-JS Git library by orders
#   of magnitude vs alternatives like `nodegit` (libgit2 native
#   binding, no browser support, complex build) or `simple-git`
#   (forks the system git binary as a subprocess).
#
#   isomorphic-git ships:
#
#     • Typed `git.init({fs, dir, bare, defaultBranch})`
#       Typed `git.clone({fs, http, dir, gitdir, url,
#         corsProxy, ref, remote, singleBranch, noCheckout,
#         noTags, depth, since, exclude, relative, headers,
#         onAuth, onAuthFailure, onAuthSuccess, onProgress,
#         onMessage})`
#     • Typed `git.add({fs, dir, gitdir, filepath, cache,
#         force, parallel})`
#     • Typed `git.commit({fs, dir, gitdir, message, author,
#         committer, signingKey, dryRun, noUpdateBranch, ref,
#         parent, tree, onSign})`
#     • Typed `git.log({fs, dir, gitdir, filepath, ref, depth,
#         since, force, follow})`
#     • Typed `git.status({fs, dir, gitdir, filepath, cache})`
#       Typed `git.statusMatrix({fs, dir, gitdir, ref,
#         filepaths, filter, cache, ignored})`
#     • Typed `git.push({fs, http, dir, gitdir, ref, remoteRef,
#         remote, url, force, delete, corsProxy, headers,
#         onAuth, onAuthFailure, onAuthSuccess, onProgress,
#         onMessage})`
#     • Typed `git.pull({fs, http, dir, gitdir, ref, url, remote,
#         remoteRef, prune, pruneTags, fastForward, fastForwardOnly,
#         corsProxy, singleBranch, headers, author, committer,
#         signingKey, onAuth, onAuthFailure, onAuthSuccess,
#         onProgress, onMessage})`
#     • Typed `git.fetch({fs, http, dir, gitdir, url, remote,
#         ref, remoteRef, singleBranch, tags, depth, relative,
#         since, exclude, prune, pruneTags, corsProxy,
#         headers, onAuth, onAuthFailure, onAuthSuccess,
#         onProgress, onMessage})`
#     • Typed `git.checkout({fs, dir, gitdir, ref, filepaths,
#         remote, noCheckout, noUpdateHead, dryRun, force,
#         track, onPostCheckout, cache})`
#     • Typed `git.merge({fs, dir, gitdir, ours, theirs,
#         fastForward, fastForwardOnly, dryRun, noUpdateBranch,
#         abortOnConflict, message, author, committer,
#         signingKey, onSign})`
#     • Typed `git.branch({fs, dir, gitdir, ref, object,
#         checkout, force})`
#       Typed `git.listBranches({fs, dir, gitdir, remote})`
#       Typed `git.currentBranch({fs, dir, gitdir, fullname,
#         test})`
#       Typed `git.deleteBranch({fs, dir, gitdir, ref})`
#     • Typed `git.tag({fs, dir, gitdir, ref, object, force})`
#       Typed `git.annotatedTag({fs, dir, gitdir, ref, message,
#         object, tagger, signingKey, onSign})`
#       Typed `git.listTags({fs, dir, gitdir})`
#     • Typed `git.resolveRef({fs, dir, gitdir, ref, depth})`
#       Typed `git.expandRef({fs, dir, gitdir, ref})`
#     • Typed `git.readBlob({fs, dir, gitdir, oid, filepath,
#         cache})`
#       Typed `git.readCommit({fs, dir, gitdir, oid, cache})`
#       Typed `git.readTree({fs, dir, gitdir, oid, filepath,
#         cache})`
#       Typed `git.readTag({fs, dir, gitdir, oid, cache})`
#       Typed `git.readObject({fs, dir, gitdir, oid, format,
#         filepath, encoding, cache})`
#       Typed `git.writeBlob({fs, dir, gitdir, blob})`
#       Typed `git.writeCommit({fs, dir, gitdir, commit})`
#       Typed `git.writeTree({fs, dir, gitdir, tree})`
#       Typed `git.writeTag({fs, dir, gitdir, tag})`
#       Typed `git.writeObject({fs, dir, gitdir, type, object,
#         format, oid, encrypt})`
#     • Typed `git.walk({fs, dir, gitdir, trees, map, reduce,
#         iterate, cache})`              the generic tree-walker
#                                        used to implement every
#                                        higher-level traversal
#     • Typed `git.WORKDIR()` / `git.STAGE()` / `git.TREE({ref})`
#                                        walker namespaces
#     • Typed `git.listFiles({fs, dir, gitdir, ref})`
#       Typed `git.listRemotes({fs, dir, gitdir})`
#       Typed `git.listNotes({fs, dir, gitdir, ref})`
#     • Typed `git.addRemote({fs, dir, gitdir, remote, url,
#         force})`
#       Typed `git.deleteRemote({fs, dir, gitdir, remote})`
#       Typed `git.getRemoteInfo({http, url, headers, forPush,
#         corsProxy, protocolVersion, onAuth, onAuthFailure,
#         onAuthSuccess})`
#       Typed `git.getRemoteInfo2({http, url, headers, forPush,
#         corsProxy, protocolVersion, onAuth, onAuthFailure,
#         onAuthSuccess})`
#     • Typed `git.indexPack({fs, dir, gitdir, filepath,
#         onProgress})`
#     • Typed `git.packObjects({fs, dir, gitdir, oids, write})`
#     • Typed `git.findMergeBase({fs, dir, gitdir, oids,
#         cache})`
#     • Typed `git.findRoot({fs, filepath})`
#     • Typed `git.hashBlob({object})`
#     • Typed `git.isDescendent({fs, dir, gitdir, oid,
#         ancestor, depth, cache})`
#     • Typed `git.isIgnored({fs, dir, gitdir, filepath})`
#     • Typed `git.stash({fs, dir, gitdir, op, message})`
#     • Typed `git.version()`
#     • Typed `git.setConfig({fs, dir, gitdir, path, value,
#         append})`
#       Typed `git.getConfig({fs, dir, gitdir, path})`
#       Typed `git.getConfigAll({fs, dir, gitdir, path})`
#       Typed Git wire-protocol v1 + v2 implementation
#                                        (the smart-HTTP +
#                                        pkt-line layer)
#     • Typed HTTP backend abstraction   (concrete typed Node +
#                                        browser fetch
#                                        implementations
#                                        shipped as `http/node`
#                                        and `http/web`)
#     • Typed `onAuth` callback chain    typed `GitAuth`
#                                        envelope:
#                                        `{username, password,
#                                        oauth2format,
#                                        token, headers,
#                                        cancel}`
#     • Typed CORS proxy support         (the
#                                        `https://cors.isomorphic-git.org`
#                                        public CORS proxy or
#                                        a self-hosted instance
#                                        of `isomorphic-git/cors-
#                                        proxy`)
#     • Typed FS abstraction (LightningFS-compatible)
#                                        backed by:
#                                        Node `fs` /
#                                        `@isomorphic-git/lightning-fs`
#                                        (IndexedDB) /
#                                        `memfs` (in-memory) /
#                                        BrowserFS (legacy) /
#                                        any LightningFS-shaped
#                                        provider
#     • Typed PGP-signed commit verification
#                                        (via @isomorphic-git/
#                                        pgp-plugin)
#     • Typed pack-format reader+writer  (the .pack + .idx
#                                        on-disk format)
#     • Typed shallow-clone support
#     • Typed delta resolution
#     • Typed `onProgress` / `onMessage` event streams
#
#   isomorphic-git is the Git library behind essentially every
#   modern JavaScript Git-aware application:
#
#     • **Logseq** — the local-first knowledge management /
#       outliner app (35,000+ ★);  uses isomorphic-git for the
#       graph-sync backend so users can git-push their local
#       graph to GitHub/GitLab without leaving the app
#     • **Insomnia** (Kong) — the open-source REST/GraphQL
#       client (38,000+ ★);  isomorphic-git for the
#       insomnia-design git-sync feature that backs request
#       collections in a git repo
#     • **WordPress Playground** — the browser-based WordPress
#       runtime;  isomorphic-git for plugin/theme
#       distribution
#     • **Umbrel** — the personal-server OS (8,000+ ★);
#       isomorphic-git for the umbreld daemon's
#       app-installation Git operations
#     • **Apache KIE Sandbox** — the Apache business-rules
#       sandbox;  isomorphic-git for the kie-sandbox-fs
#       browser-based git editor
#     • **Microsoft FluidFramework** — the real-time
#       collaboration framework (5,000+ ★);  isomorphic-git
#       in routerlicious server's git backend
#     • **JohnLindquist Script Kit** — the developer-focused
#       script launcher;  isomorphic-git for script-repo
#       management
#     • **Workrave** citool — repetitive-strain-injury
#       prevention CI tool
#     • **Starhackit** — the React+Node SaaS starter
#       template;  isomorphic-git in the server side
#     • **OpenPencil** — open-source sketchpad
#     • **Wizzi** — the polyglot code-generator framework
#     • **Cocktailpeanut/dalai** — the LLaMA installer
#       (predecessor to Pinokio)
#     • **DeepKit ML** — the typed Deep Learning framework's
#       package CLI
#     • **Strapi/Mirage AI** — the AI orchestration platform
#     • **prettier-standard** — opinionated prettier wrapper
#     • **GitVan** (this very project)
#     • Plus thousands of internal browser-based / Electron /
#       VS Code extension Git-aware tools.
#
#   The isomorphic-git project is structurally significant
#   because it enabled an entirely new class of applications:
#   browser-based Git tools (no server required), Electron
#   desktop apps with offline git-sync, VS Code web extensions
#   with git awareness, and Cloudflare-Workers / Vercel-Edge
#   git proxies.  Pre-isomorphic-git, every JS Git tool either:
#     (a) forked the `git` binary (Node-only, no browser),
#     (b) wrapped libgit2 via `nodegit` (Node-only, native
#         build dependency, no browser), or
#     (c) called a remote Git API like GitHub REST (online-only,
#         vendor-locked).
#   isomorphic-git is the first pure-JS option that works in any
#   JavaScript runtime.
#
#   Verified via:
#     gh api repos/seanchatmangpt/gitvan/contents/package.json
#       → "name": "gitvan"
#       → "bin": { "gitvan": "./dist/bin/gitvan.mjs" }
#       → "dependencies": { ..., "isomorphic-git": "^1.27.1", ... }
#     raw.githubusercontent.com seanchatmangpt/gitvan main
#         src/cli.mjs
#       → import { defineCommand, runMain } from "citty";
#       → export const cli = defineCommand({
#           meta: { name: "gitvan", ... },
#           subCommands: { daemon, event, cron, audit, hooks,
#                          workflow, jtbd, cleanroom, job,
#                          schedule, worktree, submodule,
#                          init, setup, save, ensure, pack,
#                          marketplace, scaffold, compose,
#                          chat, llm, revops, studio }})
#
#   This entry is the TS-Node=180 closing pair that **CLOSES** Axis
#   125 (pure-Rust / pure-Go / pure-JS Git protocol +
#   repository implementation taxonomy) at 1/1/1, completing the
#   triple-180 round-number landmark (Rust=180 R1073 _tms on
#   GitoxideLabs/gitoxide + Go=180 R1074 _vergo on
#   go-git/go-git + TS-Node=180 R1075 _gitvan on isomorphic-git/
#   isomorphic-git) and marking the **118th axis closed** in the
#   corpus.  R1076 on deck: Rust=181 OPENS Axis 126.
#
#   No completion for `gitvan` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
